# SCSS Style Guide

## Overview
This document outlines the best practices and conventions for writing SCSS in this project to ensure consistency, readability, and maintainability.

## BEM-like Nesting

To keep component styles organized and scoped, use a BEM-like (Block, Element, Modifier) nesting structure within your `.module.scss` files.

-   **Block:** The root selector should match the component's name (e.g., `NewAccountForm` for `NewAccountForm.tsx`).
-   **Element:** Child elements within the block should be denoted by `&_elementName`.
-   **Modifier:** Variations of a block or element should be denoted by `&--modifierName`.

This approach encapsulates all of a component's styles within a single block, making them easy to locate and understand. The `&` character ensures that the selectors are correctly compiled by SASS while keeping the source code clean.

### Example

```scss
// NewAccountForm.module.scss

.NewAccountForm {
  // This is the main block style (optional, can be empty)
  
  &_formContainer {
    // Styles for the form container element
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
  }

  &_input {
    // Styles for an input element
    font-size: 1rem;

    &--disabled {
      // Style for a disabled modifier on the input
      opacity: 0.5;
      cursor: not-allowed;
    }
  }

  &_submitButton {
    // Styles for a submit button element
    background-color: blue;
    color: white;

    &--primary {
      // Style for a primary modifier
      font-weight: bold;
    }
  }
}
```

### Corresponding Component Usage (`.tsx`)

When using these styles in a component, CSS Modules will generate unique class names, but you will access them via the keys you defined in the SCSS file.

```tsx
import styles from './NewAccountForm.module.scss';

// ...

return (
  <div className={styles.NewAccountForm}>
    <div className={styles.NewAccountForm_formContainer}>
      <input className={`${styles.NewAccountForm_input} ${styles['NewAccountForm_input--disabled']}`} />
      <button className={`${styles.NewAccountForm_submitButton} ${styles['NewAccountForm_submitButton--primary']}`}>Submit</button>
    </div>
  </div>
);
```
